## Terminal-Befehle - UTF-8 Workaround
Whenever a terminal command is executed, always prepend the command with UTF-8 encoding settings:
```
$OutputEncoding = [Console]::OutputEncoding = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8
```

All terminal commands must follow this pattern:
```powershell
$OutputEncoding = [Console]::OutputEncoding = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8; [actual command here]
```

This prevents Base64 encoding issues with environment variables containing curly braces in PowerShell.


